South Africa’s Ruling ANC Will Consider Coalition to Rule in Western Cape

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-05-03T05:33:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/south-africa-s-ruling-anc-will-consider-coalition-to-rule-in-western-cape.html
South Africa ’s ruling  African National
Congress  will consider forming a coalition with opposition
parties in order to rule in Western Cape province after
municipal elections later this month, President  Jacob Zuma  said.  Coalitions are part of the “democratic structure,” Zuma
said in a televised interview with the South African
Broadcasting Corp. today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nasreen Seria at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net  